<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN214-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai, potuviyal; tuṟai, poruṇmoḻikkāñci. avaṉ vaṭakkiruntāṉ coṟṟatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
  </div>
    <div xml:id="PN214">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>ceykuvaṅ kollō nalviṉai yeṉavē</l>
<l>yaiya maṟāar kacaṭīṇṭu kāṭci</l>
<l>nīṅkā neñcattut tuṇivil lōrē</l>
<l>yāṉai vēṭṭuva ṉāṉaiyum peṟumē</l>
<l>kuṟumpūḻ vēṭṭuvaṉ vaṟuṅkaiyum varumē</l>
<l>yataṉā, luyarnta vēṭṭat tuyarntici ṉōrkkuc</l>
<l>ceyviṉai maruṅki ṉeyta luṇṭeṉiṟ</l>
<l>ṟoyyā vulakattu nukarcciyuṅ kūṭun</l>
<l>toyyā vulakattu nukarcci yilleṉiṉ</l>
<l>māṟip piṟappi ṉiṉmaiyuṅ kūṭu</l>
<l>māṟip piṟavā rāyiṉu mimayattuk</l>
<l>kōṭuyarn taṉṉa tammicai naṭṭut</l>
<l>tītil yākkaiyoṭu māytaṟavat talaiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="2ab">For those who have not cut off the doubt </l>
<l corresp="1">as to whether they would do good work/deeds, </l>
<l corresp="2cd-3ab">in hearts from which a flaw-gathering sight has not departed </l>
<l corresp="3cd">  they are without determination. </l>
<l corresp="4">An elephant hunter will get an elephant, </l>
<l corresp="5">and a quail hunter will come [back] empty-handed. </l>
<l>Therefore, if there is attaining [their] higher desires</l>
<l>on account of the deeds done for those who are high, (6f.)</l>
<l corresp="8">enjoyment is met in the imperishable world, </l>
<l corresp="9">and if there is no enjoyment in the imperishable world, </l>
<l corresp="10">the absence of birth after changing is met. </l>
<l corresp="11a-c">If one is not born [again] after changing, </l>
<l corresp="13">the very best is being gone along with a flawless body </l>
<l corresp="11d-12">after erecting one’s fame as high as the peak of the Himālaya. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
